There‚Äôs a lot of uncertainty right now, particularly for hourly workers & small businesses. More workers are being furloughed every day, or seeing their hours drastically cut ‚Äî esp. w/ new guidance for restaurants. The economic impacts of #COVID19 are & will continue to be felt.

Missouri must, must expand Medicaid. Our state's failure to do so has forced rural hospitals and providers to close, while too many Missourians go uninsured or underinsured. The last thing we need is for people to not get tested for 
#coronavirus because of a lack of insurance.

Congress must take dramatic action now to curb the growing #COVID19 (coronavirus) outbreak. It is time that both parties come together & lead. Step one: expand paid sick leave, so people don't have to choose between supporting their families & staying home when they are sick.
